<h1>NYC Land Value Tax (LVT) Analysis</h1>

<p>This page summarizes an analysis of replacing New York City's <strong>property, personal income, and sales taxes</strong> with a <strong>land value tax (LVT)</strong> set at <em>13%</em> of land value. The LVT would be voluntary initially, allowing taxpayers to choose between the old tax system or LVT. Over time, old taxes would increase to encourage switching.</p>

<hr />

